data.meta_description:
230 likes, 0 comments - fastcompany on April 29, 2023: "Before Zappos, Tony Hsieh came up with the idea for the Internet advertising network LinkExchange with his friend Sanjay Madan.⁠
⁠
With hundreds of small business websites, LinkExchange could sell packages of banner ads across these sites to larger companies that would pay to advertise within the LinkExchange-enlisted websites. And the big VCs—and big parties—came knocking soon after.⁠
⁠
Read more about the story of @downtowntony at the link in our bio.⁠
⁠
[Photo: Michael Kovac/Getty Images for Vanity Fair]".
